de.rwth.i2.attestor.semantics.jimpleSemantics.jimple.statements.invoke

Class InvokeHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rwth.i2.attestor.main.scene.SceneObject
      • de.rwth.i2.attestor.semantics.jimpleSemantics.jimple.statements.invoke.InvokeHelper
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    InstanceInvokeHelper, StaticInvokeHelper

    public abstract class InvokeHelper
extends SceneObject
    An instance of this class is a helper for a specific invoke statement. It can be used to prepare the heap before the invoked method is executed, to add variables referencing this and the arguments of the method. After the execution of the method it can be used to remove all variables that should only be visible inside the method, e.g. references which the method did not remove and its local variables.

    Call prepareHeap(input) for the heap that initializes the method call and cleanHeap( result ) on heaps that result from the execution of the abstract Method.
    Author:
    Hannah Arndt

      • prepareHeap

        public abstract void prepareHeap(ProgramState programState)
                          throws NotSufficientlyMaterializedException
        Attaches method parameters and if need be this to the programState for use in the method.

        Exceptions may occur in the evaluation of the arguments or the calling Value cause them.

        Parameters:
        programState - : the programState which will be the input of the called method
        Throws:
        NotSufficientlyMaterializedException - if the argument or the base value can not be evaluated on the heap before it is materialized.
